ed 774.21\nunsecured 202.11 976.32\nBanking House $2900.00; Furni\nture and Fixtures 52577.73 5,477.73\nCash in vault and net amounts\ndue from Banks, Bankers\nTrust Companies 31,844.21\n$248,535.17\nLIABILITIES\nCapital stock paid in $10,000.00\nSurplus fund 10,000.00,\nUndivided profits, less current\nexpenses taxes paid 5.823.42\nNotes and Bills Rediscounted 25,665.68\nBills Payable 52,500.00\nDeposits subject to check 107,926.33\nTime certificates of deposit 36,532.61\nCashier's checks outstanding 87.13\nMrs. Stubbs Dead.\nMrs. Caroline Stubbs, wife of\nM. R. Stubbs, died of pneumonia\nat her home Jan. 6, 1921, aged\n54 years. Surviving her are her\nhusband, M. R. 'Stubbs, five\ndaughters and one son, James.\nThe daughters are Mrs. M.\nMeacham, Chattanooga, Tenn.;\nMrs. H. B. Martin, Charlotte, N.\nC; Mrs. J. B. Miller, Wilmington,\nN. C; Mrs. F. M. Bush, Yidalia,\nGa.; and Miss Ruby Stubbs, of\nRockingham. Besides her im\nmediate family there is left her\nmother, three sisters and three\nbrothers. Interment took place\nat new Eastside cemetery.\nAll that medical skill and lov\ning hands could do was done to\nrelieve the sufferer. But God\nsaw best. And we can only wait\na short while, when we shall join\nher on the other shore. Mrs\nStubbs was a devoted member\nof the Methodist church for a\nnumber of years. X\nFor Rent\nFor rent, some Rood farms near\nLittle's Mills in Richmond county\nand near Smith's Ferry in Anson\ncounty; well equipped with\ndwellings and outbuildings\nWrite or come to see me R. R\nLittle, Mangum, N. C.\nStatement of the condition of the\nRichmond County\nSavings Bank\nat Rockingham, N. C.\nat the close of business Dec. 29th, 1920.\n$248,535.17\nState of North Carolina County of Rich\nmond. Jan. 12th, 1921.\n1. Prince O'Brien, Cashier of the.\nabovenamed bank.do solemnly affirm that\nabove statement is true to the bestof my\nknowledge and belief.\nFRINCE O'BRIENr Cashier.\nSubscribed and sworn to before me,\nthis 12th day of Jan. 1921.\nC. M. iSKADY,\nNotary Public\nCorrect Attest\nDr. W. L. Howell\nJ. H. McRae\nB. B. Farlow\nDirectors.\n$258,201.80\n4 956.72\n22,600.00\n16,379.29\n120033\n10,500.00\n666.00\nRESOURCES\nLoans and discounts\nOverdrafts,\nStocks and Bonds\nCash on hand and due\nfrom banks\nCash items\nReal Estate owned\nFurniture and Fixtures\nTotal\nLIABILITIES\nCapital Stock\nSurplus\nUndivided Profits\nDividends account\nDeposits\nTotal $3U,504.14\nState of North Carolina, County of Rich\nmond,\nI. W. L. Scales. Cashier of the above\nnamed Bank, do solemnly swear that the\nabove statement is true to the best of my\nknowledge and belief.\n(Signed) W. L. SCALES, Cashier.\nSworn to and subscribed before me,\nthis the 14th day of Jan. 1921.\nH. C. PARSONS,\nNotary Public.\nCorrect Attest:\nJ. Stansill Covington\nH. C. Wall\nWilliam Entwistle\n$314,504.14\n$15,000.00\n15,000.00\n8,562 48\n112.50\n275.S65.16\nBUILD A BUILDING.\nSTATE OF NORTH CAROLINA\nDepartment of State.\nCERTIFICATE OF DISSOLUTION\nTo All to Whom These Presents\nMay Come Greeting:\nWhereas, It appears to my satis\nfaction, by authenticated record of\nthe nroceedings for the voluntary\ndissolution thereof by the unani\nmous consent of all the stockhold\ners, deposited in my office, that the\nhighway Holding company, a cor\nporation of this State, whose prin\ncipal office is situated at No.\nstreet, in the town of Rockingham,\nCounty of Richmond, State of North\nCarolina (Paul R. Younts, being the\nagent therein and in charge thereof,\nupon whom process may be served),\nhas complied with the requirements\nof ChapfW 22, Consolidated Statutes,\nentitled Corporations, preliminary\nto the issuing of this. Certificate of\nDissolution:\nNow, Therefore, I, J. Bryan\nprimes, Secretary of State of the\nState of North Carolina, do hereby\ncertify-that the said corporation did,\non the 28th day of December 1920,\nfile in my office a duly executed and\nattested consent in writing to the\ndissolution of said corporation, ex\necuted by all the stockholders\nthereof, which said consent and the\nrecord of the proceedings aforesaid\nare now on file in my said office as\nprovided by law.\nIn Testimony Whereof, I have\nhereto set my hand and affixed my\nofficial seal at Raleigh, this 28th day\nof December; A. D. 1920.\ni. BRYAN\" GRIMES,\nSecretary of State.","height":"26004","width":"17292"}}
